snippet.textDisplay: This is a folk tale from Cholistan. I am from the area. This composition is beautiful, but does not harness the pain of Sami's mother. It is a very old tale that spread among Punjab, and now Pothari people claim it. The mother of Sami was so distressed that she would chant and sing. And she would say, "I love you so much that it is my turn now to prove my love for you". She would cry so much that rain would fall on the desert. There is almost no rainfall in Cholistan and people die there. After her death, villagers would recite her song hoping to see the tears of Sami's mother..Hoping to see a cloud with rain. What a master piece..  Respect to Baba Bulleh Shah and ustaad Waris Shah.
